                                            <div class="instructions">
                                                <ol>
                                                    <li>To make sauce, spray a frying pan with oil and place over a medium-high heat.</li>
                                                    <li>Add onion, garlic and cumin. Cook, stirring, for 3-4 minutes until onion has softened.</li>
                                                    <li>Place the peas in a bowl. Use a fork to mash until coarsely crushed. Stir in the haloumi and egg. </li>
                                                    <li>Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Pour three 1/4-cupfuls of pea mixture around the pan, allowing room for spreading. </li>
